##After the closure of the city, received the mother's critical notice

Micro Signal Zhenshigushi1

Function description, every day a moving original true story.

After the outbreak of new crown pneumonia, Wuhan and other cities have been closed, living in Xiaogan, Lin Qi received seventy-year-old mother of the dying notice. To meet her mother and arrange for treatment, she made three trips back to her native Hanchuan, crossing 80 kilometers and 10 days of checkpoints. Eventually, the daughter meets the mother in the intensive-care unit.

This is the 547th story of the true story project

Year: 2020

Location: Xiaogan, Hanchuan

Year: 2020

Location: Xiaogan, Hanchuan

January 25,2:00 p.m. , ready for a nap, Lin Qi heard the phone ring, the caller is father Lin Huahui. She was celebrating the Spring Festival with her husband at his father-in-law's home in Xiaogan, Hubei Province, and had just paid her respects to her parents in Hanchuan on New Year's Eve.

On the other end of the phone, his father's voice was a little impatient: "Lin Qi, call your mother quickly. " Without waiting for her reaction, he continued, "she hasn't eaten in a few days, you persuade her. " Thinking of her mother's illness, Lin Qi immediately launched a video invitation.

A few seconds later, the face of her mother, Zhang Huiwen, appeared on the screen, her cheeks swollen on both sides. My mother responded, "I'm fine. I'm fine. " It sounded like she was coming out of the tank.

Mother this year 70 years old, 4 years ago mother midnight abdominal pain, sent to the emergency department after discharge, asked her mother, the response is also "nothing. ". This sentence, let the alarm bell ring in her heart, she decided that the mother must be a big thing. Tears, she told her mother must eat on time, the mother nodded.

She decided to go home to Hanchuan. Home away from Xiaogan 80 km, usually also more than an hour away. But now, the new crown pneumonia epidemic is severe, January 2424:00, Xiaogan has been sealed off, vehicles can not go out.

Mother Zhang Huiwen a few days to loss of appetite, day and night in bed, and afraid to go to the hospital infected with new pneumonia virus, decided to at home hard shoulder. In order to let the daughter be at ease, she also specially picked a few rice, took a picture. However, Lin Huahui found blood in the tissue of the waste basket, Zhang Huiwen prevaricated that it was a nosebleed.

By the third day of the Lunar New Year, more than 11 pm, Lin Huahui was awakened by a violent cough. He quickly got up, took the basin, around to the other side of the bed, placed under Zhang Hui Tattoo. See wife vomit mixture, Lin Huahui heart a sink, is black. In one night, Zhang Huiwen vomited five times.

After dawn, Zhang went to the town's hospital for a blood test, a chest x-ray and a spine scan. The report showed that her lungs were fine and her temperature was normal, but her cervical spine was abnormal. She was suspected of having a stroke and was referred to a higher hospital in Hanchuan. Doctors warn that a stroke, if mishandled, can cause a stroke and carry the risk of death.

But under the epidemic, all the ambulances in Hanchuan have been requisitioned, the hospital has no car to send to pick up people in the town, the town is also subject to traffic control, private cars can not leave the town at will, the town hospital can not receive. After the infusion, Zhang Huiwen can only take the anti-inflammatory drugs prescribed by the doctor, forced to go home for observation.

She was so distraught that she had to rush back to Hanchuan to bring her mother to hospital.

Vicky and her husband left the house, driving their car to try to break through the blockade.

His father was too old, too distracted to take the train alone a few years ago, and in her view, too weak to deal with the current crisis. Mother needs her by her side. The mother had already suffered a stroke and had to be taken to hospital. But now Xiaogan is surrounded by Lin Qi, high-speed railway station, high-speed and other access to leave the municipal area all closed. The city, which used to be accessible in all directions, has now been isolated as an island.

Lin Qi and her husband tried to find the weaknesses of the prevention and control system. Soon after driving on the national highway, they ran into manned checkpoints and had to take a detour. When we got to the path, although there was no one on duty, we ran into all kinds of fences and barriers, and we ran into cars parked across the road.

Like a chicken with its head cut off, it started and stopped, and finally, it had to double back.

Back at home again, Lin Qi can only guard the phone, look eagerly at the epidemic prevention and control and other information. To the meal point, Lin Qi hurriedly called her mother to see if she can eat rice, the mother also pretended to eat some. The illusion of her physical stability collapsed on February 1st: she could not swallow any more food.

Lin Qi holding a cell phone, dial the hospital's emergency phone, or get anxious refused. But under, Lin Qi sent a micro-blog, to strangers for help, her number of fans only more than 400, this time, is also useless. What Lin Qi did not expect was that a netizen left the number of the president of the People's Hospital of Hanchuan City, and she also contacted the epidemic prevention headquarters of the town, and things turned around.

Community workers found the home and confirmed that the mother was in critical condition. Lin Huahui came to epidemic prevention headquarters pass, while waiting for her daughter contact the news vehicle. Around 4:00 p.m. , he got the license plate number, and he put it on his pass.

Holding the card, Lin Huahui hurried home, and Zhang Huiwen together on the car, to the Hanchuan City People's Hospital. If all goes well, they'll be at the hospital 20 miles away in half an hour. However, the road was heavily blocked and there was some delay in getting out of the car to check in. It was a little after 5:00 when they reached their destination.

After entering the hospital, Zhang Huiwen first took a chest CT, and then in turn did kidney function, liver function and other tests. By 23:20 PM, due to high blood pressure, moderate anemia, renal dysfunction, hyperkalemia, the hospital issued a critical notice to Zhang Huiwen: "The patient is currently in critical condition, at any time may occur breathing cardiac arrest and critical life. "

Zhang Huiwen's potassium is 7.3, which means she must be put on dialysis as soon as possible or her life could be in danger, but the hospital has no dialysis equipment for her at the moment, so she has to be transferred. Lin Huahui out of control, the doctor and his treatment plan, he "what do not understand" , had to keep calling her daughter Lin Qi.

The nurses immediately pushed her into the intensive-care unit and plugged her into a vacuum, which family members could not visit. Being left outside, Lin Huahui, unable to see his wife, worried that she was alone inside, blamed his daughter: "Why should your mother sent in? "

Lin huahui insists that he should be with his wife.

Notice of the danger down, the second departure of Lin Qi. According to the regulations of Xiaogan, the family members who hold the notice of danger have the qualification of passing the customs. On her mobile phone, she received a photo of her mother's death notice, which became a token of protection for her clearance.

Ms. Lin and her husband took the route through Wuhan, which took the least amount of time. If all goes well, 70 minutes later, she will be able to meet her father. At each checkpoint, she calmly stated that her mother was dying, took out a picture of the note, confirmed it to the stranger, and repeated it.

She didn't think she would be part of the problem. Her body temperature climbed to 37.0 C during a routine customs clearance. If the body temperature is abnormal, you can't go through the checkpoint. The staff told her to stand by the car and calm down.

Three minutes later, Lin Qi perturbed to measure again, a look at the number, temperature drop, Lin Qi hurriedly on the car, continue to move forward.

When we reached the Wuhan border, the notice of danger was invalid. The staff was instructed to guard strictly, even if there is a notice of danger, Wuhan is only allowed to enter and not allowed to leave. She and her husband immediately changed their route, leaving Wuhan for Hanchuan in the direction of Yunmeng County.

She and her husband did not speak. There was silence in the car, not even a ringing cell phone. At this point, no news is the best news. We took the long way around, but we didn't hit any roadblocks. All was quiet, and at 3:30 in the morning, the map showed that the next bridge would take us to the boundary of Hanchuan.

As she neared the bridge, she had a vague sense that something was wrong. The Path was unlit, and in the darkness, the headlights lit up the obstacles ahead: not man made railings, but piles of dirt half a meter high. Notices, language, vehicles in the inanimate patch of soil before all the invalidation, the sense of despair flooded her. The fact that my mother was lying in the intensive-care unit was like a time bomb, and she didn't know how much room she had for herself.

Her mother had always been her strongest ally. Many years ago, Lin Qi remembers, she cried in the middle of the night and woke up to find her mother leaning against the bed, patting her on the back like a child. She kept saying softly, "don't be afraid, don't be afraid, mommy is here. "

At the time, her grief was instantly soothed, but now her mother was left alone in the intensive-care unit, unable even to hold her mother's hand as a daughter.

The second time the road back Xiaogan, Lin Qi sticks like a stick in the bed at home. Holding the phone in her hand, she turned the volume up as loud as she could, but she was afraid that the bell would suddenly ring and bad news would come. I keep my eyes open, hoping it's GonNa be light soon. Stay to 6:00 more, Lin Qi immediately dial the doctor's phone, to discuss the transfer of dialysis program. There is no hospital in Hanchuan, can only be transferred across the city, families need to contact their own.

In the past, patients in Hanchuan would travel to nearby Wuhan, but at a time when there were no additional medical resources, Ms. Lin prepared to transfer her mother to her home town of Xiaogan. Separated by two places, the fate of her and her mother was bound, at this time every phone call, will affect the mother's life and death.

From the network, Lin Qi collected the phone of several hospitals, first contact Xiaogan Central Hospital, Xiaogan a hospital, but they do not receive patients. Each time she dials the phone, she restates the situation, like a machine, repeating back, "like telling someone else's story. ".

She called Xiaogan Hospital of traditional Chinese medicine, which said it was fine to be transferred, but that it could not do vascular access, which is required for dialysis in patients with kidney failure. As a result, only one space hospital remains on her contact list. But for a while, the phones at the Space Hospital weren't working.

As if trapped in a tunnel, "please give me a sign to tell me what to do next, " she wrote on her Weibo Account, eight hours after her mother entered the intensive-care unit at 7:48 on Feb. 2.

Just after 9 pm, Lin huahui lingers outside the intensive-care unit. His wife was dying, and he couldn't help her. Doctors have direct contact with Lin Qi, Lin Huahui is also waiting for her daughter's call.

Although the family of critically ill patients, in the corridor has a separate bed, but Lin huahui worried about his wife, did not have a good rest. He told his father that the hospital was willing to take patients, and that the hospital on the Hanchuan side had contacted the medical department to move a machine to the bedside for dialysis.

In view of Zhang Huiwen's physical condition, Lin Huahui and Lin Qi did not handle the transfer. More than 12:00 noon, Lin Huahui in the confirmation of uremia on the document signed, Zhang Huiwen on dialysis.

Eight hours later, the first dialysis completed, Lin huahui bought eight treasure porridge, milk, nurse to send in, I heard that Zhang Huiwen eat a little, his hanging heart slightly put down some. Zhang Huiwen's blood potassium content returned to normal, creatinine dropped from 1897 to 709, Lin Huahui did not understand the meaning of the index, he can only from the daily drip, grasp the information of his wife out of danger.

On Feb. 3, when her mother underwent a second dialysis session, Lin finally felt filial piety. After contacting the Neighborhood Committee, the street office and the district headquarters in turn, she finally got the certificate from Wuhan to drive on the road again. Always busy road, this empty space, Lin Qi turned to ask her husband: "Do we like to live in a disaster movie? "

After many checkpoints, more than 2 pm, Lin Qi and her husband finally arrived at the Hanchuan People's Hospital. Zhang was still on dialysis, and near the door of the intensive care unit, she thought she heard her mother's cough. She decided that her husband would take her father home and stay with her in the hospital.

A little after 6 pm, the nurse went into the intensive-care unit to change the dressing on the patient. The door was open and the smell of disinfectant was coming out. Through the gap between the two doors, I saw the mother sitting on the bed, Lin Qi immediately shouted "Mom" , Zhang Huiwen heard, eyes turned. "Mom, you need to eat. " Zhang Huiwen said, "I told you not to come back. Why did you have to come back? " She was worried that the hospital was crowded and the risk of infection was high. The nurse shut the door and the brief conversation broke down.

After a while, Lin Qi received a phone call from his father: "Your mother has been calling me looking for you. " Lin Qi hurriedly called his mother. Originally saw her to come, Zhang Huiwen is anxious to discharge from hospital, says with Lin Qi "I am quite good" .

My mother had to stay in intensive-care unit, and even if all went well, she would need dialysis five times a week to stay alive and never leave the hospital again. Her mother never asked her for anything. As an adult, she took her mother on only three trips.

In the hospital, Lin Qi just learned the truth of the emergency 4 years ago mother, in fact, is chronic kidney disease, need timely treatment, to delay the arrival of uremia, but the mother was afraid to give her trouble, did not pour out any discomfort.

At night, Lin Qi wears a mask and sleeps in a hospital bed in the hallway. Suddenly, an old man in the ICU life indicators is not good, has been unconscious, the nurse asked the family sleeping in the bed next to her: "continue to rescue or give up treatment? "

Hearing these words, Lin Qi once again realized that death is so close to him. As her mother lay in the intensive-care unit, she realized she could not persuade others to "respect the patient's choice. " She was afraid her mother would tell her, "I'm really struggling. ".

The next day, another critically ill patient came to the hospital and transferred his mother from the ICU to the general ward. More than 10 o'clock, Lin Qi finally saw her mother up close, she was breathing oxygen, a dialysis tube inserted in the neck. She noticed that her mother's face was puffier than before.

Lin held her mother's hand tightly and asked, "is something wrong? " Zhang shook her head, denying as usual. But in fact every time dialysis, all need from the neck of the tube, first draw out two tubes of blood. Bright Red Blood ran through the tube, toxins in her body separated from the water, and vomiting and lethargy were common reactions after dialysis.

Zhang Huiwen advised her daughter: "This is a once in a lifetime, don't cry. " Sitting, she fell asleep, talking in her sleep, waving her hands and not knowing what to grasp. Waiting for the mother to sleep a bit, Lin Qi gently put the nursing bed flat, cover the quilt. Standing by the bed, she listened avidly to the sound of her mother's breathing.

For a moment, she was like a spring released from pressure. After 10 anxious days, she finally returned to her mother.

* Lin Qi, Lin Huahui and Zhang Huiwen as pseudonyms.

- END -
